<TITLE> Airport security beefed over hijack alert </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 8 (bdnews24.com)Security measures have been beefed up at Shahjalal International Airport over speculation of a plane hijacking and possible terrorist activity. Uttara zone deputy commissioner of police Nisarul Arif told bdnews24.com that the airport authority had initially informed the police that they were considering the highest alert over plane hijacking. "But later they decided to just boost security measures." Wing commander Shahidur Rahman, the airport director, said that the security measures had been enhanced. "We're in a meeting now over this matter," he told bdnews24.com. On Wednesday, an alleged Islamist threatened to blow up the parliament building. bdnews24.c
